    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @jonfowler1231 this is possible by specifying a list of beacon node addresses to the validator client separated by comma such as:\r\n\r\n`--beacon-rpc-provider=localhost:4000,localhost:4001`\r\n\r\nIt matters what beacon node you are connected to, and we recommend sticky load-balancing if you want to a highly-available setup. It is up to the operator how they wish to load balance validators and beacon nodes. We prefer stakers do not use this feature, but instead handle load balancing in their cloud infrastructure if they are running Prysm in the cloud",
